result.adr_address: 10 Gresson St, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 10 Gresson St, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: 金輝點心

reviews.text: Good food. Good value. Next to 7-11 store.

Dainty bite sizes are great for those whose wallet can accommodate dainty bites.  I have teenagers who want good food and lots of it.  Hong Kong has lots of "expert" dim sum chefs, but we love this place because it's good, local, and plentiful.  The service is all Chinese  but fast.  Ask for the English menu.  The outside is easily missed but don't.  The interior has been cleaned up.  Best of all, they have a toilet.

This is a very local dim sum place. Portions are generous and price is reasonable. HKD17 to about HKD45 for dim sum dishes. They have some other dishes like steam fish which seems to be a local favourite and the fish and winter melon soup is really nice. Location is at 49 Spring Lane, not Gresson Street.

food: ok. as expected msg but not overly salty. the “skin” of har gao (shrimp dumplings) was too thick. the turnip cake was meh. large portion.
packed and uncomfortable seating but not too noisy.
great for solo eater.
very reasonably priced. there’s set lunch during lunch hours.
Good dim sum, yummy  yummy, well, small place, you don't expect to sit comfortably

result.name: Kam Fai Dim Sum Restaurant

reviews.text: Very tasty and cheap dim sum around wan chai area. They have english menu as well which made us easy to order. Highly recommended.
Very good local experience. Owner was a great guy that bent over backwards to accommodate our party of 7

Awesome Dim Sum for early risers. This is Dim Sum pure - fresh,ply prepared, great variety and delicious. The “restaurant” is as low key as it gets, and it opens at 6 am. So you find there more local people having breakfast before work than tourists, but if you are an early riser AND you likeDim Sum, this is an awesome option.
Simple yet the best lotus leaf Lo Mai Gai so far!

Back again today.
Typical HKG DimSum joint. Good stuff n good typical atmosphere .
Old fashion small shop. Local style dim sum. No complains really
